Sorcery: Dreams of the Mad Overlord
Copyright (C) 2021 Dave Moore

Make sure the following packages/third-party libraries from the Standard and
Universe Repositories are installed:

- sfml
- sfml-dev
- libsfml-dev
- libsfml-doc
- libsqlite3-0
- libsqlite3-dev
- libjsoncpp-dev
- doxygen
- libfmt-dev
- uuid-dev
- binutils-dev
- libunwind-dev

Add the following repository:

ppa:texus/tgui-0.8

And then install the following additional package:

libtgui-dev

The additional following third-party libraries are also needed:

- simpleini https://github.com/brofield/simpleini/
- sqlite modern cpp wrapper https://github.com/SqliteModernCpp/sqlite_modern_cpp
- sfeMovie https://github.com/Yalir/sfeMovie
- Thor https://github.com/Bromeon/Thor
- Magic Enum C++ https://github.com/Neargye/magic_enum
- Backward-cpp https://github.com/bombela/backward-cpp

Note that to compile Sorcery: Dreams of the Mad Overlord requires a compiler
with C++20 support.